From the Mathlib repo root, run `lake exe cache get` to pull prebuilt oleans, then `lake build Mathlib.Module.Path` where the dotted path mirrors the file location (e.g. `Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Basic.lean` → `lake build Mathlib.Algebra.Group.Basic`). If you truly need a clean state first, remove `.lake/build` (or run `lake clean`) before `lake exe cache get`; skipping the cache forces recompilation of every transitive dependency and is rarely what you want. Ensure `lean-toolchain` matches Mathlib's pinned version (`elan` auto-installs it) and that `lakefile.lean`/`lake-manifest.json` are unmodified. Expect a few seconds when the cache covers all dependencies, or many minutes if any upstream module is dirty. Verify success by checking that `.lake/build/lib/Mathlib/Module/Path.olean` exists and `lake build` exits 0.
